                         CC DOS SHELL
                         ____________


                        FUNCTIONAL KEYS
                        ---------------


 Primary keys:
 -------------

 F1                     Help (still in russian, sorry)
 F2                     Bring USER menu to screen. The menu may be 
                        edited via the item 'menu file edit' in the 
                        pull-down menu.
 S-F2                   Bring 'main' user menu.
 F3                     View the file cursor is currently on
 S-F3                   View the file by name
 F4                     Edit the file cursor is currently on
 S-F4                   Edit the file by name
 F5                     Copy current file/directory or a group of
                        previously selected (INS key) files and 
                        directories.
 F6                     Move or rename current file/directory or a 
                        group of previously selected (INS key) files 
                        and directories.
 F7 (S-F7)              Create new subdirectory
 F8                     Delete current file/directory or a group of
                        previously selected (INS key) files and 
                        directories.
 S-F8                   Delete file/directory by name.
 F9 (or ^N)             Bring the commander pull-down menu.
 S-F10                  Bring the commander pull-down menu and 'open' 
                        it as it was opened last time.
 F10                    Quit the commander.



   Filelist navigation
   -------------------
 UP                     Move cursor up thru the filelist
 DOWN                   Move cursor up thru the filelist
 RIGHT                  Move cursor right thru the filelist
 LEFT                   Move cursor left thru the filelist
 PgDn                   Move cursor page down thru the filelist
 PgUp                   Move cursor page up thru the filelist
 ^UP                    Move screen page up
 ^DOWN                  Move screen page down
 Home                   Move cursor to the first file in the filelist
 End                    Move cursor to the last  file in the filelist

 Alt-letter             Move cursor to the file navigating by name.

 ENTER                  1) Execute a command (if exists)
                        2) Change the directory (if the cursor is on 
                           the subdirectory or on "..")
                        3) Execute the 'file_extension related' action.
                           the list of extensions and actions may be 
                           edited via 'extension file edit' item in the 
                           pull-down menu.
 S-ENTER                Execute the 'file_extension related' action.  
                        the list of extensions and actions may be 
                        edited via 'extension file edit' item in the 
                        pull-down menu.
 ^-ENTER                Execute the 'file_extension related' action.  
                        the list of extensions and actions may be 
                        edited via 'extension file edit' item in the 
                        pull-down menu.

   Note: 'file_extension related' actions may be different depending on 
   key you actually pressed !

 ^PgUp                  change to the previous directory ( CD .. )
 ^\                     change to the rout directory     ( CD \  )
 ^PgDn                  change to the subdirectory the cursor is 
                        currently on



   Select/Unselect files/directories
   ---------------------------------

 INS                    Mark/reset file/directory cursor is currently 
                        on as 'selected/non-selected'.
 Grey+                  Select all the files depending on wildcard 
                        pattern.
 Grey-                  Unselect all the files depending on wildcard 
                        pattern.
 S-Grey+                Select all the files/directories depending on 
                        wildcard pattern.  
 S-Grey-                Unselect all the files/directories depending on 
                        wildcard pattern.
 ^-F9                   Toggle 'selected/unselected' files
 S-INS                  Write all the names of the selected files into 
                        the special file 'cc.tmp' in current directory.


   Command line editing
   --------------------
 DEL                    Delete character
 BSP                    Backspace delete character
 ^INS                   Toggle 'insert mode' for the command line 
                        editing
 ^Home                  Move cursor to the command line start
 ^End                   Move cursor to the command line end
 ^Enter                 Bring the name of file/directory cursor is 
                        currently on to the command line
 S-Left (^S)            move one character left in the command line
 ^LEFT                  move one word left in the command line
 S-Right (^T)           move one character right in the command line
 ^RIGHT                 move one word right in the command line
 ^BSP                   move one word back in the command line



   Windows manipulations
   ---------------------
 TAB                    Move cursor to the NEXT window
 S-TAB                  Move cursor to the PREVIOUS window

 Alt-F1                 Set the drive for the first  window
 Alt-F2                 Set the drive for the second window
 Alt-3                  Set the drive for the third  window
 Alt-4                  Set the drive for the forth  window

 ^F1                    Toggle visibility of the window 1
 ^F2                    Toggle visibility of the window 2
 ^F3                    Toggle visibility of the window 3
 ^F4                    Toggle visibility of the window 4

 ^-F10                  Change colors of the current window. Once you 
                        pressed 'change colors' key you have to 
                        navigate the machine cursor thru the different 
                        window positions and use left/right/up/down 
                        keys to change the foreground and the 
                        background. ESC key will help you exit.

 ^F                     Toggle 'full window' status.
 ^M                     Move the window. Once you entered the 'move 
                        window' mode you may use left/right keys to 
                        move the current window and S-left/S-right keys 
                        to change the size. ESC will help you exit.

 ^P                     Toggle next window visibility.
 ^R                     Re-read current window contents.
 ^T                     Toggle next window as 'TREE'.
 ^Q                     Toggle next window as 'Quick View'.
 ^U                     Swap 'this' and the next window.


   Command stack
   -------------

 Alt-F8                 View last 'n' commands issued
 ^E                     Bring the previous command from stack to 
                        command line
 ^X                     Bring the next     command from stack to 
                        command line


   Miscellaneous
   -------------
 ESC  (^O)              1) Erase the command from the input area.
                        2) Show DOS screen.

 Alt-F3                 Alternatively view the file (internal viewer)
 Alt-F4                 Alternatively edit the file (external editor)
 Alt-F5                 Lock the screen
 Alt-F6                 View last 'n' directories used
 Alt-F7                 Fast find file on the current/all drives
 Alt-F9                 Switch 25-43 lines on EGA and VGA screens
 Alt-F10                Bring a 'tree' picture for the current drive

 S-F9                   Save the current configuration.

 ^-F6                   Rename the file/directory 'inplace'
 ^-F8                   Calculate recursively sizes of all the 
                        subdirectories.
 ^-F12                  Toggle commander trace On/Off (debugging).

 ^A                     Change the attributes of the current file.
 ^B                     Toggle key bar visibility.
 ^C                     Bring the 'configuration' menu.
 ^G                     Show EXE module header attibutes
 ^L                     Toggle 'INFO' window
 ^Z                     Toggle English-Russian text



                        MOUSE
                        -----

 Left button may be used to navigate thru files, windows, bottom bar, 
 pull-down menu, tree and so on. Double click simulates ENTER.
 You may scroll filelist, pressing button on the window up/bottom 
 lines.

 Right button may be used to select/unselect files (INS key 
 emulation).


